## 4. Shared architecture: one engine, two configs

```
intake (voice or document)
      |
      v
  job_spec.json  <-- user confirms, reused verbatim in every call
      |
      v
  call orchestrator  ---> N parallel calls (ElevenLabs Agents + Twilio/SIP)
      |                        |
      |                        v
      |                  quote_extractor (tool call mid-conversation)
      v
  negotiation round 2  <--- leverage = best verified competing quote
      |
      v
  ranked report (transcript citations, itemised fees, recommendation)
```

**What lives in code (never changes):** intake state machine, call orchestration, barge-in and friction handling, AI disclosure logic, quote schema validation, leverage selection, ranking and reporting, honesty constraints.

**What lives in the config file (per vertical):**

```yaml
vertical: bau_electrical            # or: tech_repair_industrial
job_spec_schema: ./schemas/bau_electrical.json
intake_questions:                   # what a professional estimator would ask
  - id: q1
    text: "Wie viele Quadratmeter Nutzfläche hat das Objekt?"
    maps_to: area_sqm
