## 12. Business model slide

Existing German platforms in both markets monetise the supplier: lead fees of roughly 50 to 120 euro per contact request on craft portals, or 10 to 15 percent commission models. The supplier pays whether or not the job happens, which is why suppliers price the fee back into the quote and why nobody negotiates on the buyer's behalf.

Ours: the buyer pays, either a flat fee per negotiation report or a share of verified savings. In Bau, a package where the negotiated result is 4,000 euro below the median of collected quotes supports a fee in the several-hundred-euro range and still leaves the buyer clearly ahead. In Tech Repair, the recurring nature matters more than the ticket: a maintenance department runs this several times a month, which makes it a subscription rather than a transaction.

One line for the jury: **we are the first party in this market whose incentive is aligned with the person paying the bill.**

